See also: Golden Horseshoe, National Capital Region (Canada), and Detroit–Windsor
Statistics Canada's measure of a "metro area", the Census Metropolitan Area (CMA), roughly bundles together population figures from the core municipality with those from "commuter" municipalities.[78]


