Articles from Britannica encyclopedias for elementary and high school students.Toronto - Children's Encyclopedia (Ages 8-11)Toronto is the largest city in Canada. It is also the capital of the province of Ontario. It is the cultural, trade, and financial center of the country.Toronto - Student Encyclopedia (Ages 11 and up)Located on the north shore of Lake Ontario, Toronto is Canada’s most populated city and the capital of the province of Ontario. The city is Canada’s primary financial and commercial center. It is home to the Toronto Stock Exchange and many large businesses. Toronto also is a major international trading center. Lake Ontario serves as the area’s boundary between Canada and the United States. Across the lake from Toronto is the state of New York.
